-- Boeing announces $2.7 bln Air France KLM order
-- 
-- Wed Jun 20, 2007 4:39am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/20/us-boeing-airfrance-order-idUSWLA035520070620

 

 LE BOURGET, France  (Reuters) - Boeing Co. ( BA.N ) said on Wednesday it has won an order for 16 planes from Air France KLM ( AIRF.PA ) worth a total of $2.7 billion at list prices. 

 Air France ( AIRF.PA ), France's largest carrier, ordered nine of Boeing's wide-bodied 777-300ER aircraft and took options for on a further nine. The planes are being used to replace Air France's larger 747-400 jumbos. Air France already has a fleet of 46 777s and now has a total of 14 on order. General Electric Co. ( GE.N ) is to supply the engines on the 777s, in a deal it said it was worth $450 million at list prices. At the same time KLM ordered seven of Boeing's single-aisle 737-700 planes. Both orders were already registered in Boeing's tally of firm orders, attributed to unidentified customers.